Data Insights Engineering Intern (Summer 2016)		Flatiron Health		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Our mission is to serve cancer patients and our customers by dramatically improving treatment and accelerating research. Our team is building a disruptive, oncology-specific software platform that connects cancer centers across the world on a common technology infrastructure to address key healthcare challenges. Today, the Flatiron Health OncologyCloud&amp;trade; platform includes the industry-leading electronic medical record for oncology, a first-of-its-kind analytics tool, patient portal, and integrated billing management. Our goal is to help cancer centers and life science companies leverage real-world oncology data at a scale and clinical depth never before seen, to advance cancer care and accelerate research.<br /><br />As a Data Insights Engineer, you&rsquo;ll do all things data in order to help Flatiron achieve it&rsquo;s goal to use data and technology to improve cancer care. You&rsquo;ll be the technical contact for our cancer center partners, life sciences partners, and academic partners. You&rsquo;ll work with them to understand their data and their needs. You&rsquo;ll make data functional, draw insights from it, and then visualize those insights so that they are usable by varied client audiences. This is a broad role for which we consider people from many different technical and non-technical backgrounds, but no matter where you fall in the spectrum, on this team you&rsquo;ll learn everything from how a cancer clinic works to how to program (or how to program better) in Python and Angular. You&rsquo;ll also work with our Oncologists, Medical Informaticists, and Account Executives, broadening your knowledge and abilities in all these areas. <br /> As a Data Insights Engineer you will: <ul> <li>Explore new customer opportunities and interesting ways to use data to help improve cancer treatment</li> <li>Improve medical data, help to map our internal schemas</li> <li>Partner with technical teams to build tools and products</li> <li>Analyze and visualize cancer care data for our clients in cancer clinics, academic institutions, and life sciences companies</li> <li>Become the subject matter expert on the data and its capabilities</li> </ul> About you: <ul> <li><strong>You are attending university, pursuing a BS or MS related to computer science/engineering</strong></li> <li>You are passionate about our mission to improve cancer care through data and technology</li> <li>You have experience analyzing and drawing insights from data. For example, you have experience in&amp;hellip;</li> <ul> <li>a consulting firm with a focus on data analytics and visualizations</li> <li>data analytics or an insights team at a data driven company</li> <li>an institution that regularly presents its data and findings in professional conferences and publications</li> </ul> <li>You are proficient with a query language or data flow tool (e.g. SQL) and can get the data you need from data stores</li> <li>You are highly proficient with analysis and visualization tools like R, Pandas, or Tableau</li> <li>You have one or more of &amp;hellip;</li> <li> <ul> <li>software development experience, or an understanding of software application development processes, and can work with product managers, software developers and clinicians</li> <li>proficiency in using data visualization tools to design, create and communicate key stories from complicated data</li> <li>experience with Electronic Medical Records systems, Practice Management systems, or other complex systems processing healthcare or biotechnology R &amp; D data</li> </ul> </li> <li>You are self-motivated and thrive in highly uncertain situations</li> <li>You are flexible, and adapt well to complex challenges</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Flatiron Health’s mission is to serve cancer patients and our customers by dramatically improving treatment and accelerating research. Our team is building a disruptive, oncology-specific software platform that connects cancer centers across the world on a common technology infrastructure to address key healthcare challenges. <br /><br />Today, the Flatiron Health OncologyCloud™ platform includes the industry-leading electronic medical record for oncology, a first-of-its-kind analytics tool, patient portal, and integrated billing management. Our goal is to help cancer centers and life science companies leverage real-world oncology data at a scale and clinical depth never before seen to advance cancer care and accelerate research. <br /><br />We are hiring for a number of open positions. Please visit our website for more details.</div>